        "content": "<p>I don't think I could guess what <a href=\"https://www.roc-lang.org/packages/basic-cli/Task#seq\">Task.seq</a> does based on the name alone. So I'd like to explore some other options and see what people think:</p>",
        "id": 446900711,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1719325817
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Task.chainAwait</code></p>",
        "id": 446900747,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1719325828
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Task.walkAwait</code></p>",
        "id": 446900782,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1719325838
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Feel free to suggest your own!</p>",
        "id": 446900839,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1719325852
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sidenote: I don't think the function will be used so often that we need to prioritize minimal length of the name.</p>",
        "id": 446901324,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1719325963
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I agree we don’t need to shorten it</p>",
        "id": 446902839,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1719326321
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <code>Task.sequence</code> is descriptive enough, though. It creates a task sequence from a list.</p>",
        "id": 446902880,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1719326331
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>chainAwait</code> or <code>walkAwait</code> sound to me more like what <code>loop</code> does (where you control each step)</p>",
        "id": 446903227,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1719326413
